@undermaker What, you've never seen something come out early?

@erkki554 Just because you THINK it's not big enough is no reason to... write sentences with horrible grammar and spelling. Seriously. I think you were trying to insult someone, but I have no idea WTF you said.

@Torx8: defacing downloads with your scene group adverts doesn't make you a "somebody".

@DjDede: that's a normal DVD size, having two disks would increase costs and using double layers doesn't work on all readers.  Game publishers will encode videos to a size that fits.

@lowchen: the games have to physically ship to brick-and-mortar shops, this takes time so it's done shortly before release, with a ban on selling them early.  A shop employee can open the package and upload the disk (thanks!).  People who do cracks will then use this raw DVD to, well, create a crack (good), then some 31ee+ w4r3z d00dz will slap their scene junk onto it and make a release (not so good).
